Category: Hot Job, Research - Laboratory Description Duties: Performs quality control testing. Assists Senior Quality Assurance Research Analyst in maintenance of the Quality
Assurance/Quality Control Program. Assists the development of procedures, including validating and training in these
procedures. Assists in training sessions related to the needs of the program. Establishes and performs patient monitoring
testing as designated by protocols to determine safety. Establishes, performs, and interprets other quality control testing related
to activities of program. Assists in maintenance of Quality Assurance/Quality Control program. Performs equipment
qualification and validation. Ensures that preventative maintenance schedules for all equipment are established and
maintained. Performs process validation related to all procedures in the program. Performs internal quality audits. Assists in development and maintenance of standard operating procedures. Develops standard operating procedures for all
activities within the program. Ensures that these procedures meet or exceed all relevant state and federal requirements for
handling of biological and cellular components and products. Updates procedures according to changes in clinical or laboratory
practice or regulations. Assists in training sessions related to the needs of the program. Performs other job related
duties as assigned. Qualifications: Required: Bachelor's degree in a health related field or
equivalent related experience. Required: Two years experience in clinical research or laboratory. Application Documents The following is a list of the
Required and Optional documents for this position. Please be sure to have them ready before you submit your application. Required Documents: Resume/CV Optional Documents: Cover Letter Application Information Contact: Human Resources Baylor College of Medicine Online App. Form: https://chk.tbe.taleo.net/chk01/ats/careers/requisition.jsp?org=BCM&cws=1&rid=9315 Baylor College of Medicine is an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action/Equal Access Employer. Apply through Institution's Website © Copyright 2016 Internet Employment Linkage, Inc. View Employer Profile Save to your Organizer Email a Friend Institution Overview Institutional Profile Current Openings Baylor College of Medicine Home Page Job Postings Benefits Information BCM on Facebook BCM on LinkedIn BCM on YouTube BCM on Instagram BCM - That's What It Takes Advertisement Find your next career in higher ed. Save time and get organized.
